HEADWORD: Gordiacea
<hw>Gor`di*a"ce*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL. See
<er>Gordian</er>, 1.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A division of
nematoid worms, including the hairworms or hair eels (<gen>Gordius</gen>
and <gen>Mermis</gen>). See <er>Gordius</er>, and
<xex>Illustration</xex> in Appendix.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

